    },
    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\n1. Write a program to get the `Painter` to the traffic cone based on the direction it can move:\r\n\t- In your `custom.py` file define one function to have the `Painter` move east while it can move and to turn right when it is able to move south.\r\n    - In your `custom.py` file define a second function to have the `Painter` move north while it can move and to turn right when it is able to move east.\r\n    \r\n**Reminder:** Make sure you import your `custom.py` file and save it to your backpack after adding any new functions!\r\n\r\n\r\n::: details [**Need help with your algorithm?**]\r\nHere is one approach to solving this problem.\r\n\r\n```\r\n#first function\r\nwhile the Painter can move east\r\n   move\r\n   if the Painter can move south\r\n      turn right\r\n      \r\n#second function\r\nwhile the Painter can move north\r\n   if the Painter can move east\r\n      turn right\r\n   move\r\n```\r\n:::",
    "start_sources": {
      "files": {
        "0": {
          "id": "0",
          "name": "main.py",
          "language": "py",
          "contents": "from neighborhood import Painter\n# ADD import custom BELOW\n\n\n# Create Painter object\ntrinity = Painter()\n\n# Function definition for turn right\ndef turn_right():\n  trinity.turn_left()\n  trinity.turn_left()\n  trinity.turn_left()\n\n# Function definition for turn around\ndef turn_around():\n  trinity.turn_left()\n  trinity.turn_left()\n\n# Function definition to move while painter can move\ndef move_while_can():\n  while trinity.can_move():\n    trinity.move()\n\n# Function definition to move east and turn right when there's no obstacles\ndef move_east_then_turn_if_south():\n  while trinity.can_move('east'):\n    trinity.move()\n    if trinity.can_move('south'):\n      turn_right()\n\n# Function definition to move north and turn right when there's no obstacles\ndef move_north_turn_if_east():\n  while trinity.can_move('north'):\n    if trinity.can_move('east'):\n      turn_right()\n    trinity.move()\n\n# ADD TWO NEW FUNCTION DEFINITIONS IN custom.py\n\n# ADD FUNCTION CALLS TO GET THE PAINTER TO THE TRAFFIC CONE\n",
          "folderId": "0",
          "active": true,
          "open": true
        }
      },
      "folders": {
      }
